- It's a dud.

767
00:25:01,176 --> 00:25:02,176
No way.

768
00:25:02,177 --> 00:25:03,575
- One, two...
- Two.

769
00:25:03,576 --> 00:25:05,076
- It's not a dud.
- He must have won.

770
00:25:05,776 --> 00:25:06,885
- Come on.
- What?

771
00:25:06,886 --> 00:25:09,316
It can't be this easy. He won right away.

772
00:25:10,086 --> 00:25:12,246
- This is no fun.
- Win rock-paper-scissors next time.

773
00:25:12,486 --> 00:25:14,255
- Three of us can eat, though.
- Three of us can eat.

774
00:25:14,256 --> 00:25:15,956
This heart helped me get bread.

775
00:25:16,456 --> 00:25:18,832
Usually, there's another prize right next to the winning ticket.

776
00:25:18,856 --> 00:25:20,466
(Let's see.)

777
00:25:22,766 --> 00:25:23,795
- What?
- What?

778
00:25:23,796 --> 00:25:24,995
(Se Yoon also wins right after Joon.)

779
00:25:24,996 --> 00:25:26,735
This stationery store is no fun.

780
00:25:26,736 --> 00:25:28,035
- Come on.
- That's it.

781
00:25:28,036 --> 00:25:29,465
The probability is 1 in 4.

782
00:25:29,466 --> 00:25:30,505
- What?
- Really?

783
00:25:30,506 --> 00:25:31,835
- Yes.
- So this is quite impressive.

784
00:25:31,836 --> 00:25:33,235
- There must be one in each row.
- What we did was impressive.

785
00:25:33,236 --> 00:25:35,405
- So he beat the 12-percent chance.
- Right.

786
00:25:35,406 --> 00:25:36,605
Only one more member can eat.

787
00:25:36,606 --> 00:25:38,375
The 2nd ticket in the 2nd row.

788
00:25:38,376 --> 00:25:40,885
- If you win too...
- The prizes should be here...

789
00:25:40,886 --> 00:25:41,946
Wait, no.

790
00:25:42,186 --> 00:25:43,716
- Hurry up, Jong Min.
- That's...

791
00:25:43,986 --> 00:25:45,855
- Don't look.
- Don't look.

792
00:25:45,856 --> 00:25:47,156
(He even tries to cheat.)

793
00:25:47,926 --> 00:25:48,956
Whatever.

794
00:25:50,356 --> 00:25:52,495
(What's the result?)

795
00:25:52,496 --> 00:25:54,596
- One, two, three.
- Three.

796
00:25:55,366 --> 00:25:57,536
- What is this?
- My gosh!

797
00:25:57,696 --> 00:25:59,972
The odds are 1 in 4. How come they all got the winning ticket?

798
00:25:59,996 --> 00:26:02,706
(How could Jong Min get this lucky?)

799
00:26:03,036 --> 00:26:04,635
(Including Jong Min, they drew winning tickets in a row.)

800
00:26:04,636 --> 00:26:06,575
The odds are 1 in 4. How come they all got the winning ticket?

801
00:26:06,576 --> 00:26:07,576
- That's crazy.
- Yes!

802
00:26:07,646 --> 00:26:10,445
Anyway, Se Yoon, Joon, and Jong Min will have bread.

803
00:26:10,446 --> 00:26:11,616
- Okay.
- Yes.

804
00:26:12,276 --> 00:26:15,146
(The special bread is waiting for the winners.)

805
00:26:15,886 --> 00:26:18,556
(The name of the bread came from the chimney-like shape.)

806
00:26:19,386 --> 00:26:21,886
(Chimney bread, the ultimate crispy and moist bread)

807
00:26:22,126 --> 00:26:24,325
I've never seen this before. But it looks so good.

808
00:26:24,326 --> 00:26:26,326
Do we have to tear it apart and eat it?

809
00:26:26,426 --> 00:26:27,825
- We can just go for it.
- It does look like a chimney.

810
00:26:27,826 --> 00:26:29,665
- Like this.
- My gosh, just like that?

811
00:26:29,666 --> 00:26:31,735
- It's like a roll.
- Let's cut it and eat it.

812
00:26:31,736 --> 00:26:32,935
- I've never seen it before.
- Let's cut it and eat it.

813
00:26:32,936 --> 00:26:33,965
- Okay.
- We can just cut it.

814
00:26:33,966 --> 00:26:35,035
- Yes.
- Like this.

815
00:26:35,036 --> 00:26:36,065
(Generously dipping it in the whipped cream)

816
00:26:36,066 --> 00:26:38,236
Dip it in the whipped cream like this.

817
00:26:41,146 --> 00:26:43,175
(Joon has a bite too.)

818
00:26:43,176 --> 00:26:44,176
It's good.

819
00:26:45,616 --> 00:26:46,936
You know what this reminds me of?

820
00:26:47,286 --> 00:26:50,086
When I was growing up, there was a cafe called Can More.

821
00:26:50,486 --> 00:26:52,386
- Is it sweet like their bread?
- Yes.

822
00:26:52,656 --> 00:26:54,255
- That's...
- I used to have...

823
00:26:54,256 --> 00:26:55,785
bread and cream on a swing...

824
00:26:55,786 --> 00:26:57,346
when I went on a date in middle school.

825
00:26:57,596 --> 00:27:00,026
The bread and the cream were unlimited there.

826
00:27:00,796 --> 00:27:01,796
I love it.

827
00:27:01,996 --> 00:27:03,165
I used to eat Ppappao.

828
00:27:03,166 --> 00:27:06,266
This tastes just like it did when I was in middle school.

829
00:27:08,036 --> 00:27:09,596
- What is it?
- That car looks amazing.

830
00:27:10,376 --> 00:27:12,335
- I know someone who has this car.
- It's Grandeur.

831
00:27:12,336 --> 00:27:13,435
- Is this part of the exhibition?
- What is it?

832
00:27:13,436 --> 00:27:15,205
- It's a very old car.
- Will we be riding them?

833
00:27:15,206 --> 00:27:16,675
(At that moment, the members are surprised by something.)

834
00:27:16,676 --> 00:27:17,745
Cameras are installed in them.

835
00:27:17,746 --> 00:27:18,775
- Both teams...
- My goodness.

836
00:27:18,776 --> 00:27:19,815
- What is it?
- This...

837
00:27:19,816 --> 00:27:21,045
- Aren't these stick shifts?
- What's going on?

838
00:27:21,046 --> 00:27:22,216
This is incredible.

839
00:27:23,656 --> 00:27:25,856
(Speaking of these cars)

840
00:27:26,416 --> 00:27:28,285
(Breathtaking rounded curves...)

841
00:27:28,286 --> 00:27:30,456
(And strong and distinct personalities)

842
00:27:31,056 --> 00:27:34,726
(Everyone's dream car in the 1990s)

843
00:27:35,166 --> 00:27:36,665
(The 1996 Espero)

844
00:27:36,666 --> 00:27:38,666
(The 1994 LeMans Penta 5)

845
00:27:38,936 --> 00:27:40,696
It looks like you guys are in a music video.

846
00:27:41,636 --> 00:27:43,836
- These are stick shifts.
- An old music video.

847
00:27:43,976 --> 00:27:46,076
- It looks nice.
- It's GT.

848
00:27:46,136 --> 00:27:47,346
- My gosh.
- Come.

849
00:27:48,046 --> 00:27:49,105
This is amazing.

850
00:27:49,106 --> 00:27:51,416
- Are we taking two cars?
- DinDin, will you be driving?

851
00:27:51,546 --> 00:27:52,575
- Can you drive it?
- I think we're taking one car.

852
00:27:52,576 --> 00:27:55,022
- I got my license with this.
- Do you have your driver's license?

853
00:27:55,046 --> 00:27:56,215
I can drive a manual car.

854
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:58,816
I used to drive a stick shift all the way to Busan.

855
00:27:59,356 --> 00:28:00,436
This should be okay, right?

856
00:28:00,786 --> 00:28:02,586
I don't think I can get in. It's too cramped.

857
00:28:02,686 --> 00:28:04,886
- It has a nice vibe.
- Was this car always this small?

858
00:28:05,026 --> 00:28:06,586
Joon, it looks like you're in your car.

859
00:28:06,626 --> 00:28:07,866
- Right?
- Yes.

860
00:28:08,966 --> 00:28:10,395
The driver's window doesn't roll down.

861
00:28:10,396 --> 00:28:12,136
Here it is. Isn't this it?

862
00:28:12,436 --> 00:28:13,735
(A stick shift still feels unfamiliar to him.)

863
00:28:13,736 --> 00:28:15,016
- This is it.
- This must be it.

864
00:28:15,366 --> 00:28:17,336
- It's going down.
- Like that?

865
00:28:18,706 --> 00:28:20,245
(Starting with the gearshift)

866
00:28:20,246 --> 00:28:23,576
(An old car where everything is manual)

867
00:28:24,246 --> 00:28:27,286
(The windows have to be rolled down to open.)

868
00:28:27,616 --> 00:28:28,745
- This is...
- I wish I had a cassette tape.

869
00:28:28,746 --> 00:28:30,456
You have to roll down the window by hand.

870
00:28:31,086 --> 00:28:33,585
Mister, do you have any cassette tapes like "Inkigayo?"

871
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:34,885
- Cassette tape...
- This is fascinating.

872
00:28:34,886 --> 00:28:36,086
The cassette player is empty.

873
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:37,726
It doesn't go all the way down.

874
00:28:37,826 --> 00:28:38,856
There's one.

875
00:28:39,826 --> 00:28:40,926
"New Hits."

876
00:28:41,296 --> 00:28:42,395
It has "Hayeoga."

877
00:28:42,396 --> 00:28:44,642
(Se Yoon finds a cassette tape in the glove compartment.)

878
00:28:44,666 --> 00:28:47,236
(Feeling anxious that the song might not play)

879
00:28:48,066 --> 00:28:51,776
(As soon as the song plays, a smile spreads across his face.)

880
00:28:52,206 --> 00:28:53,276
Let's go.

881
00:28:53,336 --> 00:28:54,975
Let's go to Children's Grand Park.

882
00:28:54,976 --> 00:28:56,696
(Feeling ecstatic, let's go all out today.)

883
00:28:56,906 --> 00:28:58,845
(With fluttering hearts, they set out to the next destination.)

884
00:28:58,846 --> 00:29:01,116
- Lower the side-view mirror.
- Lower it, and let's go.

885
00:29:01,486 --> 00:29:03,806
- Step on it gradually.
- I don't have to change them yet.

886
00:29:03,956 --> 00:29:05,015
No.

887
00:29:05,016 --> 00:29:06,415
- After going like this...
- You can change to second gear now.

888
00:29:06,416 --> 00:29:08,132
Once you're rolling, you can shift to second gear.

889
00:29:08,156 --> 00:29:10,636
When it starts to rattle, ease the clutch. Don't slam it down.

890
00:29:10,756 --> 00:29:12,895
Keep your foot on it while pressing the brake together.

891
00:29:12,896 --> 00:29:15,095
Handle it gently.

892
00:29:15,096 --> 00:29:16,365
- It's like...
- That's important to know.

893
00:29:16,366 --> 00:29:18,235
- So you have to...
- Right.

894
00:29:18,236 --> 00:29:19,835
- feel it.
- Of course.

895
00:29:19,836 --> 00:29:21,505
It's like the blues. You pull it all the way...

896
00:29:21,506 --> 00:29:22,835
- It's not simply driving.
- and release it.

897
00:29:22,836 --> 00:29:25,575
- There's some kind of exchange.
- Of course.

898
00:29:25,576 --> 00:29:27,945
Se Yoon, it's been over 20 years, but you know it very well.

899
00:29:27,946 --> 00:29:30,376
- You're a good teacher.
- Not being afraid is important.

900
00:29:30,516 --> 00:29:31,575
Even though it's your first day,

901
00:29:31,576 --> 00:29:32,845
- you're doing very well.
- Really?

902
00:29:32,846 --> 00:29:34,286
You're doing well on your first day.

903
00:29:34,886 --> 00:29:37,786
Drive slowly. Don't mess around.

904
00:29:38,616 --> 00:29:39,686
Look straight.

905
00:29:40,016 --> 00:29:41,056
Second gear.

906
00:29:41,726 --> 00:29:43,425
This is really nice.

907
00:29:43,426 --> 00:29:45,346
(Old cars are the best. Joon is in his element.)

908
00:29:45,456 --> 00:29:48,366
Back in the day when everyone headed home for the holidays,

909
00:29:49,126 --> 00:29:51,535
traffic would get jammed. People would end up cooking...

910
00:29:51,536 --> 00:29:53,366
- on the side of the road.
- Right.

911
00:29:53,666 --> 00:29:54,766
On their way back home.

912
00:29:54,906 --> 00:29:59,576
(Roads were completely jammed during the holidays.)

913
00:29:59,936 --> 00:30:02,346
(From Seoul to Busan, it took up to 16 hours.)

914
00:30:02,906 --> 00:30:05,346
(Having tea on the road was a given.)

915
00:30:05,916 --> 00:30:08,816
(People even played yutnori to pass the time.)

916
00:30:09,716 --> 00:30:11,016
My dad was a taxi driver.

917
00:30:11,516 --> 00:30:13,185
Taxis had a special vibe...

918
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:15,326
of a stick shift.

919
00:30:15,726 --> 00:30:18,556
My dad drove a Pony back then.

920
00:30:19,996 --> 00:30:22,366
I remember riding his taxi.

921
00:30:23,666 --> 00:30:25,735
People back then were probably excellent drivers.

922
00:30:25,736 --> 00:30:26,796
Definitely.

923
00:30:28,036 --> 00:30:30,336
- A long time ago...
- It doesn't exist, does it?

924
00:30:30,476 --> 00:30:32,776
Back in the 90s, I was in a choir for a while.

925
00:30:33,006 --> 00:30:34,605
I was in a choir at my high school.

926
00:30:34,606 --> 00:30:36,706
Seniors from different clubs at school would...

927
00:30:37,216 --> 00:30:38,846
pair us up with each other.

928
00:30:39,576 --> 00:30:41,386
During orientation, we met...

929
00:30:41,616 --> 00:30:42,986
and sang together.

930
00:30:43,786 --> 00:30:45,785
Also, some people paired up...

931
00:30:45,786 --> 00:30:48,255
and became couples.

932
00:30:48,256 --> 00:30:49,816
Did you ever manage to be with someone?

933
00:30:50,996 --> 00:30:51,996
No.

934
00:30:52,556 --> 00:30:54,725
I told you. His wife is his first love.

935
00:30:54,726 --> 00:30:56,072
(Be quiet, Seon Ho. Don't be tactless.)

936
00:30:56,096 --> 00:30:57,335
No one chose me.

937
00:30:57,336 --> 00:30:58,612
(Suddenly, the atmosphere gets serious.)

938
00:30:58,636 --> 00:31:00,766
My choir senior and I were the only ones left behind.

939
00:31:02,566 --> 00:31:04,035
While patting me on the shoulder, he said,

940
00:31:04,036 --> 00:31:05,075
"Se Yoon,"

941
00:31:05,076 --> 00:31:07,905
"I'll coordinate the numbers better next time."

942
00:31:07,906 --> 00:31:08,946
I said, "It's okay."

943
00:31:09,306 --> 00:31:11,575
Are we having a group blind date today?

944
00:31:11,576 --> 00:31:12,845
(They arrive at the destination while chatting.)

945
00:31:12,846 --> 00:31:13,886
Let's get out.

946
00:31:14,146 --> 00:31:15,986
Let's go, DinDin. Thank you for driving.

947
00:31:16,316 --> 00:31:17,655
This is great.

948
00:31:17,656 --> 00:31:19,415
It would've been nicer if the weather was better.

949
00:31:19,416 --> 00:31:21,786
Since it rained earlier, the air is very clean.

950
00:31:22,056 --> 00:31:23,925
- Right.
- There must be a lot of fish here.

951
00:31:23,926 --> 00:31:25,926
- There are a lot of fish.
- There are many birds.

952
00:31:26,426 --> 00:31:28,166
- Here we come.
- Let's take photos.

953
00:31:28,366 --> 00:31:29,965
- Can you take a photo of me?
- Okay.

954
00:31:29,966 --> 00:31:31,635
We're in the 90s. This mobile phone can't exist.

955
00:31:31,636 --> 00:31:33,635
This mobile phone isn't appropriate. This is not right.

956
00:31:33,636 --> 00:31:34,636
I already took it.

957
00:31:35,466 --> 00:31:36,766
Come on. Take a photo of me.

958
00:31:37,436 --> 00:31:39,736
- I already took one.
- It should be a digital camera.

959
00:31:40,006 --> 00:31:41,076
Here we go.

960
00:31:41,976 --> 00:31:43,496
You should take it with an old camera.

961
00:31:43,816 --> 00:31:44,876
I want a photo too.

962
00:31:45,446 --> 00:31:47,046
- I'll take one with this.
- Who's next?

963
00:31:48,146 --> 00:31:49,515
(Putting on a big smile)

964
00:31:49,516 --> 00:31:51,456
- He wants to send the photo.
- I think so.

965
00:31:52,216 --> 00:31:54,555
Those who are definitely with someone take a photo like this.

966
00:31:54,556 --> 00:31:55,625
(It's sad for no reason.)

967
00:31:55,626 --> 00:31:57,506
- You took it to send it to her too.
- Exactly.

968
00:31:57,956 --> 00:32:00,765
(I love you, angel.)

969
00:32:00,766 --> 00:32:04,035
Everyone, this place was built along the clear Cheongdocheon.

970
00:32:04,036 --> 00:32:06,395
- Cheongdocheon.
- It's a train-themed park.

971
00:32:06,396 --> 00:32:07,405
That's nice.

972
00:32:07,406 --> 00:32:09,835
You can enjoy the peaceful nature here,

973
00:32:09,836 --> 00:32:12,306
so it's a popular spot for family outings.

974
00:32:12,536 --> 00:32:13,735
I can see why.

975
00:32:13,736 --> 00:32:15,705
There's clean air, and there are many activities.

976
00:32:15,706 --> 00:32:17,216
Yes, there are many things to see.

977
00:32:17,416 --> 00:32:19,876
We're back in the 90s. It's a symbol of retro travel.

978
00:32:20,016 --> 00:32:21,646
A train ride is a must.

979
00:32:21,816 --> 00:32:22,945
That sounds great.

980
00:32:22,946 --> 00:32:24,546
- We rode the train a lot.
- Definitely.

981
00:32:24,716 --> 00:32:25,855
Did people ride the train a lot in the 90s?

982
00:32:25,856 --> 00:32:26,856
- Of course.
- Yes.

983
00:32:26,857 --> 00:32:28,855
Whenever we went on trips, retreats, or Gangchon,

984
00:32:28,856 --> 00:32:30,455
we took the train from Gyeonggang Station.

985
00:32:30,456 --> 00:32:32,125
- Or Cheongnyangni Station.
- Daeseong Station.

986
00:32:32,126 --> 00:32:33,972
We met up at Cheongnyangni Station and took the train.

987
00:32:33,996 --> 00:32:38,096
(The train is filled with memories of family and friends.)

988
00:32:39,796 --> 00:32:42,306
The train is the symbol of retreats.

989
00:32:42,506 --> 00:32:45,306
You'll ride a mini train for the next mission.

990
00:32:45,836 --> 00:32:48,046
This is a line from a coffee commercial in the 90s.

991
00:32:48,976 --> 00:32:50,646
- I'm getting off here.
- I...

992
00:32:50,816 --> 00:32:52,015
- I am...
- Getting off here.

993
00:32:52,016 --> 00:32:53,515
- I'm getting off this time.
- This time.

994
00:32:53,516 --> 00:32:55,286
- Is that from a coffee commercial?
- Yes.

995
00:32:55,586 --> 00:32:57,385
You'll play a retro game challenge...

996
00:32:57,386 --> 00:32:59,256
with three stations.

997
00:32:59,456 --> 00:33:01,685
The 1st team to win 2 rounds will take the victory.

998
00:33:01,686 --> 00:33:03,246
- Okay.
- The best of three wins today.

999
00:33:03,526 --> 00:33:06,256
The winning team will be given ten time capsules.

1000
00:33:06,626 --> 00:33:08,365
- I'm glad we have already won ten.
- Yes.

1001
00:33:08,366 --> 00:33:10,172
- We must win ten no matter what.
- Of course.

1002
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:11,465
Before you arrive at the station,

1003
00:33:11,466 --> 00:33:13,136
you will hear an announcement.

1004
00:33:13,236 --> 00:33:14,835
After listening to the announcement carefully,

1005
00:33:14,836 --> 00:33:17,136
pick the player for the round.

1006
00:33:17,506 --> 00:33:18,746
When you arrive at the station,

1007
00:33:18,976 --> 00:33:21,075
the player will get off first.

1008
00:33:21,076 --> 00:33:22,746
- Okay, get ready to get off.
- Now...

1009
00:33:23,276 --> 00:33:24,576
Please board the train.

1010
00:33:25,076 --> 00:33:26,245
Here's our mini train.

1011
00:33:26,246 --> 00:33:27,585
(I'm getting off this time.)

1012
00:33:27,586 --> 00:33:28,785
- Two of us.
- In the front.

1013
00:33:28,786 --> 00:33:29,946
Do we sit with our team?

1014
00:33:30,956 --> 00:33:33,516
(Team Jong Min gets on.)

1015
00:33:34,156 --> 00:33:35,186
It's cramped.

1016
00:33:36,226 --> 00:33:38,426
- I feel bad for them.
- I know.

1017
00:33:38,956 --> 00:33:39,956
Gosh, it's cramped.

1018
00:33:39,957 --> 00:33:41,465
(Packed)

1019
00:33:41,466 --> 00:33:43,026
(Crumpled)

1020
00:33:43,966 --> 00:33:44,966
All right.

1021
00:33:45,636 --> 00:33:47,096
I hope the train is very fast.

1022
00:33:51,106 --> 00:33:52,175
It's moving.

1023
00:33:52,176 --> 00:33:53,535
(The mini train sets off.)

1024
00:33:53,536 --> 00:33:54,546
We're moving.

1025
00:33:56,106 --> 00:33:57,616
It'd be a fun place for children.

1026
00:33:57,976 --> 00:33:59,115
Once you see it...

1027
00:33:59,116 --> 00:34:00,436
- What's this?
- What's going on?

1028
00:34:00,916 --> 00:34:02,316
We entered a tunnel.

1029
00:34:03,316 --> 00:34:04,356
This is fun.

1030
00:34:04,616 --> 00:34:05,655
It's a tunnel.

1031
00:34:05,656 --> 00:34:08,526
This train is entering a tunnel.

1032
00:34:08,686 --> 00:34:10,555
It's exiting the tunnel.

1033
00:34:10,556 --> 00:34:11,725
(After going through a tunnel, )

1034
00:34:11,726 --> 00:34:13,155
(they see the first station right away.)

1035
00:34:13,156 --> 00:34:14,542
We're approaching the first station.

1036
00:34:14,566 --> 00:34:17,766
This station is Brain Station.

1037
00:34:18,296 --> 00:34:21,365
Please have one player get off after the train comes...

1038
00:34:21,366 --> 00:34:22,865
- to a complete stop.
- What station is this?

1039
00:34:22,866 --> 00:34:24,205
- Brain.
- Brain.

1040
00:34:24,206 --> 00:34:25,476
It's over for the other team.

1041
00:34:25,676 --> 00:34:26,876
- I'll go.
- Go ahead.

1042
00:34:27,036 --> 00:34:28,345
- Brain.
- Brain?

1043
00:34:28,346 --> 00:34:29,645
Why did they team us up?

1044
00:34:29,646 --> 00:34:31,215
- We don't have any brains.
- This is ridiculous.

1045
00:34:31,216 --> 00:34:33,445
Aren't you smarter than me? You're creative at least.

1046
00:34:33,446 --> 00:34:34,616
- What?
- You're creative.

1047
00:34:35,086 --> 00:34:37,145
Please get off now if you're stopping at Brain Station.

1048
00:34:37,146 --> 00:34:38,185
- Okay.
- Good luck.

1049
00:34:38,186 --> 00:34:39,315
I'll be back.

1050
00:34:39,316 --> 00:34:40,996
Who's coming out? Why are you getting off?

1051
00:34:41,286 --> 00:34:42,646
- Why are you getting off?
- What?

1052
00:34:42,826 --> 00:34:45,026
Did you come out because you have no brain?

1053
00:34:45,126 --> 00:34:47,026
Jong Min, this isn't Brainless Station.

1054
00:34:47,256 --> 00:34:48,665
Let's go, Jong Min.

1055
00:34:48,666 --> 00:34:50,126
- I can do it.
- Everyone.

1056
00:34:50,366 --> 00:34:51,736
Round One at Brain Station.

1057
00:34:52,066 --> 00:34:53,896
- The game category is...
- What is it?

1058
00:34:54,106 --> 00:34:55,736
Upside-down stone flicking.

1059
00:34:56,466 --> 00:34:58,105
(Stone flicking)

1060
00:34:58,106 --> 00:35:00,945
(A classic childhood game that everyone used to play)

1061
00:35:00,946 --> 00:35:03,246
- Upside-down stone flicking?
- Please reveal it.

1062
00:35:03,676 --> 00:35:05,146
What is upside-down stone flicking?

1063
00:35:05,316 --> 00:35:06,316
Stone flicking?

1064
00:35:06,317 --> 00:35:09,346
(Inversion tables and an omok board)

1065
00:35:09,786 --> 00:35:11,715
- They must play upside-down.
- Those in the train,

1066
00:35:11,716 --> 00:35:12,885
please get off.

1067
00:35:12,886 --> 00:35:14,446
What does it have to do with the brain?

1068
00:35:14,786 --> 00:35:16,686
I can't do this.

1069
00:35:17,286 --> 00:35:19,126
- Can we switch players?
- No.

1070
00:35:19,896 --> 00:35:22,226
I think Jong Min has to switch with someone else.

1071
00:35:22,426 --> 00:35:23,525
He got fat injected under his eyes,

1072
00:35:23,526 --> 00:35:25,135
so he can't have blood rushes under them.

1073
00:35:25,136 --> 00:35:26,195
(Even the other team is worried about his eyes.)

1074
00:35:26,196 --> 00:35:27,365
You should tell him.

1075
00:35:27,366 --> 00:35:29,106
- Can I switch?
- Is it true?

1076
00:35:29,206 --> 00:35:31,105
- What happens with a blood rush?
- My eyes will bleed.

1077
00:35:31,106 --> 00:35:32,575
(His eyes will bleed if he's upside-down?)

1078
00:35:32,576 --> 00:35:33,705
Due to the surgical procedure,

1079
00:35:33,706 --> 00:35:34,845
do you want to replace the player?

1080
00:35:34,846 --> 00:35:35,846
- Yes.
- "Due to the surgical procedure?"

1081
00:35:35,847 --> 00:35:36,875
By the way...

1082
00:35:36,876 --> 00:35:38,076
- All right, everyone.
- Okay.

1083
00:35:38,276 --> 00:35:39,415
Let me explain why this is Brain Station.

1084
00:35:39,416 --> 00:35:40,445
Hanging upside down increases...

1085
00:35:40,446 --> 00:35:42,385
blood flow to the brain.

1086
00:35:42,386 --> 00:35:45,156
It helps you think clearly and focus better.

1087
00:35:45,286 --> 00:35:47,115
The two of you will face off...

1088
00:35:47,116 --> 00:35:48,886
in a stone flicking match with sharp focus.

1089
00:35:49,686 --> 00:35:50,725
Players.

1090
00:35:50,726 --> 00:35:52,125
(Upside-down stone flicking on 2 Days 1 Night)

1091
00:35:52,126 --> 00:35:53,155
Please enter.

1092
00:35:53,156 --> 00:35:54,365
- Players are entering.
- Here we go.

1093
00:35:54,366 --> 00:35:55,495
- Here we go.
- Gosh.

1094
00:35:55,496 --> 00:35:56,896
Good luck.

1095
00:35:57,126 --> 00:35:58,295
Say hello to each other.

1096
00:35:58,296 --> 00:36:00,266
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

1097
00:36:00,366 --> 00:36:02,505
(DinDin, 9th dan, responsible for the brains and teeth)

1098
00:36:02,506 --> 00:36:03,812
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1099
00:36:03,836 --> 00:36:05,976
Say hello. Who will go first?

1100
00:36:06,506 --> 00:36:07,575
Are you playing first?

1101
00:36:07,576 --> 00:36:09,845
(Lee Joon plays first.)

1102
00:36:09,846 --> 00:36:10,846
Here I go.

1103
00:36:10,847 --> 00:36:12,916
The increased blood flow will clear their mind.

1104
00:36:13,046 --> 00:36:15,115
Nice. He has white stones.

1105
00:36:15,116 --> 00:36:17,385
- What?
- You touched it. I'm sorry.

1106
00:36:17,386 --> 00:36:18,386
- Black stones are up next.
- He missed...

1107
00:36:18,387 --> 00:36:19,455
his flick.

1108
00:36:19,456 --> 00:36:20,515
There he goes.

1109
00:36:20,516 --> 00:36:21,525
(Moving a tiny bit)

1110
00:36:21,526 --> 00:36:23,226
- What are you doing?
- It's slippery.

1111
00:36:23,626 --> 00:36:25,325
They started a reconnaissance.

1112
00:36:25,326 --> 00:36:26,555
- This is difficult.
- They aren't aggressive.

1113
00:36:26,556 --> 00:36:28,295
- You can't touch it twice.
- It's hard.

1114
00:36:28,296 --> 00:36:29,325
Okay.

1115
00:36:29,326 --> 00:36:31,366
(Joon's stone falls off the board.)

1116
00:36:31,536 --> 00:36:33,695
- Gosh.
- One of his stones fell.

1117
00:36:33,696 --> 00:36:35,436
You might as well hit him on the face.

1118
00:36:35,936 --> 00:36:36,966
(Upset)

1119
00:36:37,106 --> 00:36:38,176
Black stones.

1120
00:36:38,476 --> 00:36:40,706
One of the stones got lost. What about DinDin?

1121
00:36:41,346 --> 00:36:42,946
DinDin's flick was passive.

1122
00:36:43,476 --> 00:36:45,546
Okay, I'll start now.

1123
00:36:45,916 --> 00:36:47,956
(It's Joon's turn with the upside-down blood flow.)

1124
00:36:48,246 --> 00:36:49,516
What are you doing, Joon?

1125
00:36:50,486 --> 00:36:52,155
(Remaining stones, Joon: 3, DinDin: 5)

1126
00:36:52,156 --> 00:36:53,355
- His stone flew off...
- Hey, this is...

1127
00:36:53,356 --> 00:36:54,856
- the board.
- I can't make it move.

1128
00:36:55,156 --> 00:36:56,485
Try it. Flick it harder.

1129
00:36:56,486 --> 00:36:57,825
Now...

1130
00:36:57,826 --> 00:36:59,556
(DinDin's stone falls off.)

1131
00:36:59,826 --> 00:37:00,896
Okay.

1132
00:37:01,926 --> 00:37:03,926
You're still ahead by one.

1133
00:37:04,336 --> 00:37:05,856
Joon, I can see your nostrils clearly.

1134
00:37:06,536 --> 00:37:08,906
(Totally focused despite his teammate's banter)

1135
00:37:10,506 --> 00:37:13,076
(Joon's stones fall off 3 consecutive times.)

1136
00:37:13,176 --> 00:37:14,246
- Gosh.
- Darn it.

1137
00:37:14,346 --> 00:37:16,975
Are you trying to be suicidal?

1138
00:37:16,976 --> 00:37:17,976
Like this.

1139
00:37:18,216 --> 00:37:19,645
(This is DinDin.)

1140
00:37:19,646 --> 00:37:20,816
- Okay.
- Okay.

1141
00:37:20,916 --> 00:37:22,046
Keep doing it.

1142
00:37:22,316 --> 00:37:23,415
(DinDin's successful offense)

1143
00:37:23,416 --> 00:37:24,586
Keep doing it.

1144
00:37:25,386 --> 00:37:27,386
(The perfect 1 shot, 1 kill)

1145
00:37:27,786 --> 00:37:28,786
He made one.

1146
00:37:28,787 --> 00:37:30,625
What are you doing? You killed all of your stones.

1147
00:37:30,626 --> 00:37:32,955
- Time-out. Get up.
- Help him up.

1148
00:37:32,956 --> 00:37:34,056
This is crazy.

1149
00:37:36,026 --> 00:37:37,125
What are you doing?

1150
00:37:37,126 --> 00:37:38,365
(Coach Kim is giving pressure with his eyes.)

1151
00:37:38,366 --> 00:37:39,435
- Joon.
- Let me explain.

1152
00:37:39,436 --> 00:37:40,665
I already won.

1153
00:37:40,666 --> 00:37:41,666
(DinDin is sure about winning.)

1154
00:37:41,667 --> 00:37:43,636
Move your stone to the center.

1155
00:37:44,036 --> 00:37:45,036
Put it at the center.

1156
00:37:45,037 --> 00:37:46,635
- All you can do is defend.
- Okay.

1157
00:37:46,636 --> 00:37:47,956
- Don't make offense.
- I got it.

1158
00:37:48,306 --> 00:37:49,445
- Are you the coach?
- Yes.

1159
00:37:49,446 --> 00:37:50,446
What is your strategy?

1160
00:37:50,447 --> 00:37:52,515
We're determined to destroy DinDin's face.

1161
00:37:52,516 --> 00:37:53,516
- Destroy his face?
- Yes.

1162
00:37:53,517 --> 00:37:54,985
You're determined to rearrange his face.

1163
00:37:54,986 --> 00:37:56,985
That's your plan. Rearranging his face.

1164
00:37:56,986 --> 00:37:59,415
- Rearranging the front teeth.
- They're back. It's Joon's turn.

1165
00:37:59,416 --> 00:38:00,416
(Will Team Jong Min turn the tables?)

1166
00:38:00,417 --> 00:38:02,285
All right. The current score is 4 to 1.

1167
00:38:02,286 --> 00:38:03,785
- That's it.
- It doesn't move forward.

1168
00:38:03,786 --> 00:38:05,125
Put it in the center.

1169
00:38:05,126 --> 00:38:06,226
Okay.

1170
00:38:06,756 --> 00:38:08,626
(DinDin's stone falls off.)

1171
00:38:08,766 --> 00:38:09,766
(This is good.)

1172
00:38:09,767 --> 00:38:10,935
Towards the center.

1173
00:38:10,936 --> 00:38:12,736
- Can I flick it like this?
- Of course.

1174
00:38:13,266 --> 00:38:14,305
That's it.

1175
00:38:14,306 --> 00:38:16,082
- I didn't think we could do that.
- It wasn't bad.

1176
00:38:16,106 --> 00:38:17,165
(Both of them are serious about stone flicking.)

1177
00:38:17,166 --> 00:38:19,205
No, hit it gently.

1178
00:38:19,206 --> 00:38:20,435
- Keep it short.
- Darn it.

1179
00:38:20,436 --> 00:38:21,676
What?

1180
00:38:21,706 --> 00:38:22,905
(He's cornered.)

1181
00:38:22,906 --> 00:38:24,275
- Push both of them.
- What are you doing?

1182
00:38:24,276 --> 00:38:25,956
- What are you doing?
- Push both of them.

1183
00:38:26,446 --> 00:38:28,145
Use only the stone.

1184
00:38:28,146 --> 00:38:29,445
- It doesn't look stable.
- He can't reach it.

1185
00:38:29,446 --> 00:38:31,355
- That's not it.
- He can't reach it.

1186
00:38:31,356 --> 00:38:32,955
You can't reach it.

1187
00:38:32,956 --> 00:38:34,086
His arm is too short.

1188
00:38:34,286 --> 00:38:37,026
(DinDin's stone falls off.)

1189
00:38:37,826 --> 00:38:39,355
(Unbelievable)

1190
00:38:39,356 --> 00:38:40,925
- Wait a minute.
- Oh, no.

1191
00:38:40,926 --> 00:38:44,266
- Time-out.
- This is good. I can do it.

1192
00:38:44,836 --> 00:38:46,435
(Remaining stones, Joon: 1, DinDin: 2)

1193
00:38:46,436 --> 00:38:48,435
Do you know at which angle you flicked it?

1194
00:38:48,436 --> 00:38:49,605
You were looking at somewhere else.

1195
00:38:49,606 --> 00:38:50,905
It's hard to aim for it.

1196
00:38:50,906 --> 00:38:52,676
You must dominate the center...

1197
00:38:52,976 --> 00:38:54,405
to escape in any direction. Got it?

1198
00:38:54,406 --> 00:38:56,605
- Just try to seduce him.
- Seduce him.

1199
00:38:56,606 --> 00:38:58,716
The score was 4 to 1, but it's 2 to 1 now.

1200
00:38:58,916 --> 00:38:59,945
Who's next?

1201
00:38:59,946 --> 00:39:01,946
(The game resumes.)

1202
00:39:01,986 --> 00:39:02,986
All right.

1203
00:39:02,987 --> 00:39:04,886
- Towards the center. It's not bad.
- Darn it.

1204
00:39:05,756 --> 00:39:06,916
Towards the center.

1205
00:39:07,156 --> 00:39:08,326
Don't attack him.

1206
00:39:08,486 --> 00:39:10,526
Towards the center. Go.

1207
00:39:10,586 --> 00:39:11,756
It's 2 to 1.

1208
00:39:13,696 --> 00:39:14,726
Okay.

1209
00:39:15,366 --> 00:39:16,395
What have you done?

1210
00:39:16,396 --> 00:39:19,435
As a result, Team Se Yoon wins.

1211
00:39:19,436 --> 00:39:21,105
(Team Se Yoon wins the upside-down stone flicking.)

1212
00:39:21,106 --> 00:39:22,735
If Jong Min had played this game,

1213
00:39:22,736 --> 00:39:23,736
his eyes definitely bled.

1214
00:39:24,136 --> 00:39:26,035
- A lot of blood rushed to my eyes.
- Really?

1215
00:39:26,036 --> 00:39:27,675
- Let's go to the next station.
- My goodness.

1216
00:39:27,676 --> 00:39:28,805
- Okay.
- Let's go.

1217
00:39:28,806 --> 00:39:29,945
- We're on a roll.
- The train

1218
00:39:29,946 --> 00:39:32,716
(Team Se Yoon with strong momentum)

1219
00:39:32,946 --> 00:39:33,946
Let's go.

1220
00:39:33,947 --> 00:39:35,622
(Team Jong Min must win at the next station.)

1221
00:39:35,646 --> 00:39:37,085
I don't think we can go back to the future.

1222
00:39:37,086 --> 00:39:39,155
(They set out to the second station.)

1223
00:39:39,156 --> 00:39:40,316
Maybe we can't.

1224
00:39:40,356 --> 00:39:42,196
We might not be able to go back to the future.

1225
00:39:42,526 --> 00:39:43,526
What?

1226
00:39:43,527 --> 00:39:45,595
They have someone smart, someone who can run,

1227
00:39:45,596 --> 00:39:46,796
and someone who's strong.

1228
00:39:47,156 --> 00:39:48,396
- We...
- We have nothing.

1229
00:39:48,496 --> 00:39:49,596
(Laughing)

1230
00:39:49,926 --> 00:39:51,435
Why are we on the same team?

1231
00:39:51,436 --> 00:39:52,635
I know.

1232
00:39:52,636 --> 00:39:53,666
(Mutual distrust)

1233
00:39:53,796 --> 00:39:55,306
What's up next? It's a playground.

1234
00:39:56,636 --> 00:39:58,035
- We're going to a playground.
- Is that so?

1235
00:39:58,036 --> 00:39:59,036
(A slight view of the second station)

1236
00:39:59,036 --> 00:40:00,036
To the playground...

1237
00:40:00,136 --> 00:40:03,375
This station is Physical Strength Station.

1238
00:40:03,376 --> 00:40:04,376
Physical strength?

1239
00:40:04,377 --> 00:40:06,416
(Physical Strength Station)

1240
00:40:06,916 --> 00:40:09,022
- It's Physical Strength Station.
- Physical strength?

1241
00:40:09,046 --> 00:40:11,786
Two players from each team.

1242
00:40:12,116 --> 00:40:13,655
It's about physical strength.

1243
00:40:13,656 --> 00:40:14,656
(He's not confident about his physical strength.)

1244
00:40:14,657 --> 00:40:15,855
- If it requires endurance...
- You and I should play.

1245
00:40:15,856 --> 00:40:16,956
Okay.

1246
00:40:17,156 --> 00:40:19,726
This time, there's less pressure to win.

1247
00:40:20,056 --> 00:40:22,766
You'll be good when it comes to physical strength.

1248
00:40:23,426 --> 00:40:24,895
- You did gymnastics.
- Right.

1249
00:40:24,896 --> 00:40:25,896
(Team Jong Min is ahead in physical strength.)

1250
00:40:25,897 --> 00:40:28,065
This time, we have the upper hand.

1251
00:40:28,066 --> 00:40:29,136
Okay.

1252
00:40:29,336 --> 00:40:30,435
Let's do our best.

1253
00:40:30,436 --> 00:40:31,575
(Soon, the train stops at Physical Strength Station.)

1254
00:40:31,576 --> 00:40:35,246
It's raining lightly at Physical Strength Station

1255
00:40:35,346 --> 00:40:36,546
Is that a mat?

1256
00:40:36,676 --> 00:40:38,316
- I'm worried.
- If there's a mat...

1257
00:40:38,376 --> 00:40:40,346
This will be intense.

1258
00:40:40,416 --> 00:40:43,316
Everyone, you're at Physical Strength Station.

1259
00:40:43,458 --> 00:40:45,013
You're at Physical Strength Station.

1260
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:48,023
The game category at Physical Strength Station is...

1261
00:40:48,563 --> 00:40:49,722
one-legged fight.

1262
00:40:49,723 --> 00:40:50,793
(One-legged fight)

1263
00:40:51,433 --> 00:40:54,933
(The one-legged fight we used to play on the school playground)

1264
00:40:55,003 --> 00:40:56,432
It can't simply be a one-legged fight.

1265
00:40:56,433 --> 00:40:57,433
Is it the original one-legged fight?

1266
00:40:57,434 --> 00:40:59,532
It's not the original one-legged fight.

1267
00:40:59,533 --> 00:41:01,149
- That's right.
- We must protect the king.

1268
00:41:01,173 --> 00:41:04,243
- It'll be couple one-legged fight.
- What's that?

1269
00:41:04,913 --> 00:41:06,442
Byung Jin's one leg...

1270
00:41:06,443 --> 00:41:07,513
- What?
- Gosh.

1271
00:41:07,943 --> 00:41:09,142
- What?
- What's that?

1272
00:41:09,143 --> 00:41:12,252
The person in the front has to cross his arms.

1273
00:41:12,253 --> 00:41:15,422
The one in the back has to keep one leg up...

1274
00:41:15,423 --> 00:41:19,022
and grab the other person's bent leg.

1275
00:41:19,023 --> 00:41:20,823
(The couple's teamwork is essential.)

1276
00:41:20,863 --> 00:41:24,162
- They're really good.
- He looks like Kim Byung Man...

1277
00:41:24,163 --> 00:41:25,603
- with his leg up.
- Hey, Byung Man.

1278
00:41:26,293 --> 00:41:27,732
Isn't that Byung Man?

1279
00:41:27,733 --> 00:41:29,062
(It doesn't look easy.)

1280
00:41:29,063 --> 00:41:30,102
From Team Se Yoon...

1281
00:41:30,103 --> 00:41:32,332
DinDin will play to make us win.

1282
00:41:32,333 --> 00:41:33,433
That's not fair.

1283
00:41:33,703 --> 00:41:36,179
- We're playing three rounds anyway.
- DinDin can't play again.

1284
00:41:36,203 --> 00:41:37,412
Why are we teamed up?

1285
00:41:37,413 --> 00:41:39,442
- It's totally unfair.
- You're going easy on them.

1286
00:41:39,443 --> 00:41:40,472
(Exploding with complaints)

1287
00:41:40,473 --> 00:41:41,543
Come on.

1288
00:41:41,883 --> 00:41:45,182
DinDin, why don't you play a fair referee of the game?

1289
00:41:45,183 --> 00:41:46,283
Okay.

1290
00:41:46,513 --> 00:41:47,953
Aren't we playing with the shoes on?

1291
00:41:48,583 --> 00:41:50,722
- We'll win by holding it. Run away.
- Right.

1292
00:41:50,723 --> 00:41:51,823
Then they'll collapse.

1293
00:41:51,993 --> 00:41:54,123
(His body can barely hold on.)

1294
00:41:54,223 --> 00:41:55,522
Let's play without running away.

1295
00:41:55,523 --> 00:41:56,662
(Don't run away.)

1296
00:41:56,663 --> 00:41:57,992
Our strategy is running away.

1297
00:41:57,993 --> 00:41:59,269
It's not easy to stand with one leg.

1298
00:41:59,293 --> 00:42:00,763
- Here we go.
- Let's start.

1299
00:42:00,833 --> 00:42:01,833
Which way will you go?

1300
00:42:01,834 --> 00:42:03,703
Get into your positions.

1301
00:42:03,903 --> 00:42:04,903
Start.

1302
00:42:04,904 --> 00:42:06,972
When people in the back raise their leg, you'll start.

1303
00:42:06,973 --> 00:42:09,143
Get ready, set, go.

1304
00:42:10,043 --> 00:42:11,612
Hey, Joon.

1305
00:42:11,613 --> 00:42:13,693
(Team Se Yoon charges forward without wasting time.)

1306
00:42:14,383 --> 00:42:15,442
(If we hold on, they'll collapse on their own.)

1307
00:42:15,443 --> 00:42:16,982
Turn the opposite way.

1308
00:42:16,983 --> 00:42:18,583
- Destroy them.
- Turn the opposite way.

1309
00:42:19,953 --> 00:42:23,322
- What?
- What happened?

1310
00:42:23,323 --> 00:42:24,952
(What?)

1311
00:42:24,953 --> 00:42:26,299
- I mean...
- What's wrong with you?

1312
00:42:26,323 --> 00:42:28,922
(Se Yoon approached the two who were holding on.)

1313
00:42:28,923 --> 00:42:32,493
(Se Yoon used Seon Ho to press them down.)

1314
00:42:32,933 --> 00:42:35,833
(Smashing them overwhelmingly)

1315
00:42:36,103 --> 00:42:38,373
(They fell down like autumn leaves.)

1316
00:42:38,433 --> 00:42:40,942
- It's because Se Yoon is so strong.
- I know.

1317
00:42:40,943 --> 00:42:42,572
He pushed him from the back.

1318
00:42:42,573 --> 00:42:43,603
What?

1319
00:42:43,903 --> 00:42:46,219
- He pushed Seon Ho from the back.
- I didn't use any strength.

1320
00:42:46,243 --> 00:42:48,542
He lifted my leg like this.

1321
00:42:48,543 --> 00:42:49,543
(Flying in the air)

1322
00:42:49,544 --> 00:42:51,452
This is impossible to defeat.

1323
00:42:51,453 --> 00:42:53,013
He makes you fly off.

1324
00:42:53,153 --> 00:42:54,453
I'll kill you if you run away.

1325
00:42:54,783 --> 00:42:55,783
He's so scary.

1326
00:42:56,023 --> 00:42:58,193
- Please lift your leg.
- Push them right away.

1327
00:42:58,823 --> 00:43:00,423
Are you confident about hitting my calf?

1328
00:43:00,553 --> 00:43:01,862
- He's scary.
- If you do, you'll be dead meat.

1329
00:43:01,863 --> 00:43:02,863
- Okay.
- Immediately.

1330
00:43:02,864 --> 00:43:04,533
Please play slowly.

1331
00:43:04,893 --> 00:43:05,962
I'm so scared.

1332
00:43:05,963 --> 00:43:07,032
Start.

1333
00:43:07,033 --> 00:43:08,102
Run away.

1334
00:43:08,103 --> 00:43:10,032
A one-ton truck is coming.

1335
00:43:10,033 --> 00:43:12,132
(A truck weighing 8 tons with a broken steering wheel)

1336
00:43:12,133 --> 00:43:14,472
He's so scary.

1337
00:43:14,473 --> 00:43:16,273
(As expected, Team Jong Min can only defend.)

1338
00:43:17,273 --> 00:43:19,472
(Team Jong Min is cornered.)

1339
00:43:19,473 --> 00:43:20,613
He's so scary.

1340
00:43:21,043 --> 00:43:23,682
(A collision)

1341
00:43:23,683 --> 00:43:24,783
Hey.

1342
00:43:27,853 --> 00:43:30,383
(However, they held on.)

1343
00:43:32,653 --> 00:43:35,623
(Wrecked on the 2nd impact)

1344
00:43:35,993 --> 00:43:37,092
(Laughing)

1345
00:43:37,093 --> 00:43:39,833
Take a photo of it like Eul Yong Ta.

1346
00:43:40,333 --> 00:43:42,063
How could this be...

1347
00:43:42,233 --> 00:43:43,233
What is this?

1348
00:43:43,234 --> 00:43:45,109
- There was an accident.
- Do it like Eul Yong Ta.

1349
00:43:45,133 --> 00:43:47,233
See? I should have played instead.

1350
00:43:48,003 --> 00:43:49,442
- It'd been a proper game...
- It's impossible to play.

1351
00:43:49,443 --> 00:43:50,872
If I had played.

1352
00:43:50,873 --> 00:43:52,442
Try to play against him.

1353
00:43:52,443 --> 00:43:53,872
Didn't we win the second round?

1354
00:43:53,873 --> 00:43:55,112
This is the last round.

1355
00:43:55,113 --> 00:43:56,113
(Team Se Yoon: 2, Team Jong Min: 0)

1356
00:43:56,114 --> 00:43:57,212
Let's hurry and play the last round.

1357
00:43:57,213 --> 00:43:58,713
Could you switch players?

1358
00:43:58,813 --> 00:44:00,153
Please switch players.

1359
00:44:00,183 --> 00:44:01,353
Okay.

1360
00:44:01,653 --> 00:44:03,783
It's best 3 out of 5. We need to win 1 more.

1361
00:44:04,323 --> 00:44:05,763
We have a chance to turn the tables.

1362
00:44:06,323 --> 00:44:07,869
Joon, we just need to win three rounds.

1363
00:44:07,893 --> 00:44:09,013
Will you stand in the front?

1364
00:44:09,463 --> 00:44:10,522
You should've agreed...

1365
00:44:10,523 --> 00:44:12,263
when I told you that I'd play.

1366
00:44:12,893 --> 00:44:15,302
You weren't happy about it.

1367
00:44:15,303 --> 00:44:17,902
DinDin, show them. Get ready.

1368
00:44:17,903 --> 00:44:20,402
If Team Se Yoon wins again,

1369
00:44:20,403 --> 00:44:23,142
Team Se Yoon will be the final winner.

1370
00:44:23,143 --> 00:44:24,143
(Team Jong Min is in need of a win.)

1371
00:44:24,144 --> 00:44:25,743
Everyone, cock-a-doodle-doo.

1372
00:44:26,013 --> 00:44:27,173
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1373
00:44:27,513 --> 00:44:28,812
(This time, Team Jong Min moves first.)

1374
00:44:28,813 --> 00:44:31,713
Push them down first. Push him.

1375
00:44:32,653 --> 00:44:34,152
(Team Se Yoon held on.)

1376
00:44:34,153 --> 00:44:35,153
That's good.

1377
00:44:35,154 --> 00:44:36,453
Push them out.

1378
00:44:36,883 --> 00:44:38,652
Push them out. Darn it.

1379
00:44:38,653 --> 00:44:40,523
Keep your arms crossed.

1380
00:44:40,593 --> 00:44:43,723
(It's a petty fight.)

1381
00:44:45,833 --> 00:44:46,933
Push them out now.

1382
00:44:47,433 --> 00:44:48,533
Collide with them.

1383
00:44:48,833 --> 00:44:50,702
- Push them out.
- Go and hit them.

1384
00:44:50,703 --> 00:44:52,032
(A feeble knee strike)

1385
00:44:52,033 --> 00:44:53,373
Your knee.

1386
00:44:53,673 --> 00:44:54,673
Go and hit them.

1387
00:44:54,674 --> 00:44:55,772
(Joon pushes them off.)

1388
00:44:55,773 --> 00:44:56,842
Collide with them.

1389
00:44:56,843 --> 00:44:58,012
(Staggering)

1390
00:44:58,013 --> 00:44:59,743
(They collapse on their own.)

1391
00:45:00,013 --> 00:45:02,143
(A totally pathetic defeat)

1392
00:45:02,213 --> 00:45:05,513
- We won.
- We just need to win three rounds.

1393
00:45:05,983 --> 00:45:07,352
- Let's play right away.
- Come on.

1394
00:45:07,353 --> 00:45:09,153
- He pushed me like this.
- Bring it on.

1395
00:45:09,583 --> 00:45:10,923
- Come on.
- DinDin.

1396
00:45:11,053 --> 00:45:12,223
I'll stand behind you.

1397
00:45:12,823 --> 00:45:14,263
- Behind me?
- Yes.

1398
00:45:14,623 --> 00:45:16,893
(He came to finish the game.)

1399
00:45:17,193 --> 00:45:18,193
This won't work.

1400
00:45:18,194 --> 00:45:19,332
(Furious)

1401
00:45:19,333 --> 00:45:20,902
- Let's go.
- Gosh, this is bad.

1402
00:45:20,903 --> 00:45:22,802
(Please spare us.)

1403
00:45:22,803 --> 00:45:24,433
Don't you have a reserve player?

1404
00:45:24,473 --> 00:45:26,603
- No.
- Is it just the two of you?

1405
00:45:27,073 --> 00:45:29,373
Why did you pick 1 sick player and 1 old player?

1406
00:45:29,943 --> 00:45:31,072
We just need to win two more rounds.

1407
00:45:31,073 --> 00:45:32,343
- Two more.
- We won once.

1408
00:45:32,913 --> 00:45:33,913
(The 8-ton truck is starting his engine.)

1409
00:45:33,914 --> 00:45:34,983
This is hard.

1410
00:45:35,043 --> 00:45:36,313
Is the opposite side okay?

1411
00:45:36,643 --> 00:45:39,153
(He's ready to throw him.)

1412
00:45:39,413 --> 00:45:41,522
Get ready. Let's start right away.

1413
00:45:41,523 --> 00:45:42,982
(Will they be able to overcome the truck weighing 8 tons?)

1414
00:45:42,983 --> 00:45:45,352
- Ready, set, go.
- Let's just push.

1415
00:45:45,353 --> 00:45:46,693
- Let's go.
- We must go.

1416
00:45:46,953 --> 00:45:49,022
(Surprisingly, Team Jong Min charges forward.)

1417
00:45:49,023 --> 00:45:50,462
Goodness.

1418
00:45:50,463 --> 00:45:51,733
(A face-to-face clash)

1419
00:45:52,093 --> 00:45:54,433
(The terrifying 8-ton truck approaches.)

1420
00:45:54,803 --> 00:45:55,803
Goodness.

1421
00:45:57,203 --> 00:46:00,173
(DinDin is in the air.)

1422
00:46:00,273 --> 00:46:03,073
(Please spare DinDin.)

1423
00:46:04,043 --> 00:46:06,443
(It's a close call.)

1424
00:46:07,543 --> 00:46:09,943
(Right then, Joon attacks Se Yoon.)

1425
00:46:10,313 --> 00:46:12,213
(Taken aback)

1426
00:46:12,283 --> 00:46:14,423
(Team Se Yoon is falling back for now.)

1427
00:46:14,483 --> 00:46:15,552
- Gosh.
- Wait.

1428
00:46:15,553 --> 00:46:16,553
Hey.

1429
00:46:18,123 --> 00:46:20,592
(While Se Yoon was running away in a panic, )

1430
00:46:20,593 --> 00:46:23,323
(Joon pushed him!)

1431
00:46:23,563 --> 00:46:27,093
(Team Jong Min wins Round 4.)

1432
00:46:27,233 --> 00:46:28,332
Team Jong Min wins.

1433
00:46:28,333 --> 00:46:29,579
(Team Se Yoon 2 versus Team Jong Min 2)

1434
00:46:29,603 --> 00:46:32,002
(They tied it up in an instant.)

1435
00:46:32,003 --> 00:46:34,203
- The score is 2 to 2 now.
- What was that?

1436
00:46:34,543 --> 00:46:37,273
He's so light that our attacks don't really work.

1437
00:46:37,643 --> 00:46:39,549
He should've pressed him down when I lifted his leg.

1438
00:46:39,573 --> 00:46:40,573
Okay.

1439
00:46:40,574 --> 00:46:41,712
The score is 2 to 2.

1440
00:46:41,713 --> 00:46:43,353
- It's 2 to 2.
- This is the final match.

1441
00:46:43,483 --> 00:46:45,083
Continue the match when they're tired.

1442
00:46:45,453 --> 00:46:46,453
I'm so exhausted.

1443
00:46:46,613 --> 00:46:48,283
Se Yoon, stand in the front.

1444
00:46:48,383 --> 00:46:49,383
I'll stand in the front.

1445
00:46:49,383 --> 00:46:50,383
(But they're up against an 8-ton truck.)

1446
00:46:50,384 --> 00:46:51,722
- All right. Let's go.
- We should fight one more time.

1447
00:46:51,723 --> 00:46:53,423
- Let's begin.
- We should win this round.

1448
00:46:54,323 --> 00:46:55,422
Ready, go.

1449
00:46:55,423 --> 00:46:58,063
(The final match has started.)

1450
00:46:58,193 --> 00:47:00,793
- Let's go and catch the wild boar.
- Press him down.

1451
00:47:00,863 --> 00:47:01,932
Gosh.

1452
00:47:01,933 --> 00:47:04,233
(Right then, Se Yoon pushes Joon hard.)

1453
00:47:04,473 --> 00:47:06,733
(Stumbling)

1454
00:47:07,273 --> 00:47:08,273
Gosh.

1455
00:47:09,273 --> 00:47:11,113
(Joon managed to hold out.)

1456
00:47:11,273 --> 00:47:13,473
(My gosh. He's monstrously strong.)

1457
00:47:13,613 --> 00:47:15,243
(Se Yoon spots Joon being off guard.)

1458
00:47:15,743 --> 00:47:17,913
(He charges straight for Joon's weak spot.)

1459
00:47:22,553 --> 00:47:25,953
(Unbelievable)

1460
00:47:26,253 --> 00:47:28,863
(What an unbelievable upset.)

1461
00:47:29,163 --> 00:47:31,793
(What just happened?)

1462
00:47:32,033 --> 00:47:33,933
(Se Yoon charged for Joon's weak spot.)

1463
00:47:33,963 --> 00:47:36,903
(And Joon dodged the attack.)

1464
00:47:37,163 --> 00:47:40,233
(Se Yoon lost his balance, leading to his defeat.)

1465
00:47:40,333 --> 00:47:42,043
We caught the wild boar!

1466
00:47:42,873 --> 00:47:44,973
(Imitating a wild boar)

1467
00:47:45,243 --> 00:47:47,573
- They held out well as a team.
- Right.

1468
00:47:47,913 --> 00:47:49,143
All right, everyone.

1469
00:47:49,883 --> 00:47:51,282
Team Jong Min won.

1470
00:47:51,283 --> 00:47:52,829
(Team Jong Min wins the Physical Strength Station round.)

1471
00:47:52,853 --> 00:47:55,022
I should've beat them. I'm sorry, guys.

1472
00:47:55,023 --> 00:47:56,559
- Don't be.
- You don't have to apologize.

1473
00:47:56,583 --> 00:47:58,692
Let's go to the next station.

1474
00:47:58,693 --> 00:47:59,693
(They'll have the final match at the last station.)

1475
00:47:59,694 --> 00:48:00,793
Let's win the next round.

1476
00:48:00,963 --> 00:48:02,763
- Let's go.
- We caught a big fish.

1477
00:48:04,363 --> 00:48:05,392
Let's go.

1478
00:48:05,393 --> 00:48:06,639
(They set off to the last station.)

1479
00:48:06,663 --> 00:48:08,603
- We might win.
- Absolutely.

1480
00:48:09,463 --> 00:48:11,332
- I was sure we'd lose.
- Right.

1481
00:48:11,333 --> 00:48:12,333
(Team Jong Min's confidence soared after that massive turnaround.)

1482
00:48:12,334 --> 00:48:13,974
You can never predict how things will go.

1483
00:48:14,643 --> 00:48:17,872
This stop is Destiny Station.

1484
00:48:17,873 --> 00:48:19,042
- "Destiny?"
- I don't know what we'll be doing.

1485
00:48:19,043 --> 00:48:21,642
(Destiny Station)

1486
00:48:21,643 --> 00:48:23,382
One member from each team will participate in the game.

1487
00:48:23,383 --> 00:48:26,113
Please get off the train when it comes to a complete stop.

1488
00:48:26,413 --> 00:48:28,013
Let's check our daily fortune for today.

1489
00:48:30,223 --> 00:48:32,052
It says I will get a chance to finally speak my mind...

1490
00:48:32,053 --> 00:48:33,753
and do what I've always wanted today.

1491
00:48:34,323 --> 00:48:35,922
- You're lucky today? You should go.
- Then you should go.

1492
00:48:35,923 --> 00:48:36,962
(DinDin, the luckiest man on the team, will play the game.)

1493
00:48:36,963 --> 00:48:38,833
One member from each team, right?

1494
00:48:39,363 --> 00:48:40,683
- One member, right?
- "Destiny?"

1495
00:48:40,763 --> 00:48:41,902
One member from each team.

1496
00:48:41,903 --> 00:48:43,632
(Lee Joon)

1497
00:48:43,633 --> 00:48:46,232
(It's actually Jong Min!)

1498
00:48:46,233 --> 00:48:47,903
I made it this far thanks to good luck.

1499
00:48:49,203 --> 00:48:50,742
I checked my daily fortune for today.

1500
00:48:50,743 --> 00:48:51,942
(His opponent is today's luckiest man.)

1501
00:48:51,943 --> 00:48:53,273
All right. Listen up.

1502
00:48:53,613 --> 00:48:56,383
The game you'll play in Round Three at Destiny Station is...

1503
00:48:56,913 --> 00:48:59,053
(Right then, the train starts moving.)

1504
00:48:59,453 --> 00:49:00,733
- Wait. What?
- What's going on?

1505
00:49:01,023 --> 00:49:03,253
- Where are they taking us?
- Where are they going?

1506
00:49:03,653 --> 00:49:04,693
Where are we going?

1507
00:49:05,153 --> 00:49:06,453
Jong Min, you've got this!

1508
00:49:07,223 --> 00:49:09,363
- DinDin, make sure to win!
- I'm destined to win.

1509
00:49:09,593 --> 00:49:11,762
- It must be bound to the last stop.
- What's going on?

1510
00:49:11,763 --> 00:49:12,832
(What kind of mission could it be?)

1511
00:49:12,833 --> 00:49:15,602
The game you'll play in Round Three at Destiny Station is...

1512
00:49:15,603 --> 00:49:17,533
Heart-Pounding Name Compatibility.

1513
00:49:18,403 --> 00:49:20,672
Write two people's names letter by letter,

1514
00:49:20,673 --> 00:49:22,202
and add up the number of strokes...

1515
00:49:22,203 --> 00:49:24,042
to check their compatibility.

1516
00:49:24,043 --> 00:49:26,642
It's a name compatibility test that kids used to play back in the day.

1517
00:49:26,643 --> 00:49:28,813
(88 points, a fantastic match)

1518
00:49:28,913 --> 00:49:32,782
Before the train completes its loop and returns to this station,

1519
00:49:32,783 --> 00:49:35,282
you must find the person...

1520
00:49:35,283 --> 00:49:36,963
with the highest name compatibility score.

1521
00:49:37,023 --> 00:49:40,322
- DinDin, go with Lim Cheol.
- Okay.

1522
00:49:40,323 --> 00:49:42,222
- Can I choose any staff member?
- Yes, anyone will be fine.

1523
00:49:42,223 --> 00:49:44,433
